706520f-b.title: Brooklyn: Rockaway Parkway - Avenue J
706520f-b.text:
(1)
Rockaway Parkway, west side, south of Ave. J, showing the Plymouth Con-
gregational Church, which was organised in 1888.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, Note the outhouse which in a few years, with the extension of
modern sanitation, will no longer be seen in Greater New York. A view of
a small church not named on the maps of 1929.
July 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same, showing the B.M.T. Rockaway Trolley track.
July 6, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
